I just came from the future, and let me tell you, you're not going to believe what happens next!"The bartender, unimpressed, replies, "Oh yeah? What happens next?"The time traveler grins. "You're going to give me this drink for free."The bartender scoffs. "And why would I do that?"The time traveler leans in conspiratorially. "Because in exactly five minutes, a talking dog is going to walk in here, order a martini, and pay with a twenty-dollar bill he pulls from behind his ear."The bartender rolls his eyes, but a few minutes later, sure enough, a golden retriever ambles in, hops onto a stool, and in a clear, articulate voice, says, "I'll have a dry martini, shaken, not stirred."The bartender, flabbergasted, mixes the drink. The dog then reaches a paw behind his ear, pulls out a crisp twenty-dollar bill, and hands it to the bartender.The bartender, utterly stunned, stares at the dog, then at the twenty, then back at the dog. Finally, he turns to the time traveler and says, "You know what? You got your free drink. But tell me, is that dog a good tipper?"The time traveler sips his drink. "Nah, he's terrible. In my time, he's known as the 'Canine Cheapskate.' But honestly, that's not even the most unbelievable part."The bartender, still reeling, asks, "What could possibly be more unbelievable than a talking dog paying with a twenty?"The time traveler leans back, a twinkle in his eye. "He paid with a twenty-dollar bill he pulled from behind his ear. I specifically told him to use a fifty!"
